description: TO ADOPT THE RESOLUTION PROVIDING THAT THE PRESIDENT BE RE- QUESTED TO LAY BEFORE THE SENATE, COPIES OF COMMUNICATIONS FROM THE EMPEROR OF RUSSIA, OFFERING HIS MEDITATION TO BRING ABOUT PEACE BETWEEN THE UNITED STATES, AND GREAT BRITAIN, TOGETHER WITH COIES OF ANSWERS TO SUCH COMMUNICATIONS.

TO ADOPT THE RESOLUTION PROVIDING THAT THE PRESIDENT BE RE- QUESTED TO CAUSE TO BE LAID BEFORE THE SENATE, THE CORRES- PONDENCE WHICH MAY HAVE PASSED BETWEEN THE UNITED STATES AND THE KING OF SWEDEN, RESPECTING THE INTERCHANGE OF PUBLIC MINISTERS.

TO REFER TO A SELECT COMMITTEE, THE NOMINATIONS OF ALBERT GALLATIN, JOHN QUINCY ADAMS AND JAMES A. BAYARD TO BE ENVOYS EXTRAORDINARY AND MINISTERS PLENIPOTENTIARY, TO NEGOTIATE AND SIGN A TREATY OF COMMERCE WITH GREAT BRITAIN AND RUSSIA.

TO ADOPT THE RESOLUTION, PROVIDING THAT IN THE OPINION OF THE SENATE, THE POWERS AND DUTIES OF THE SECRETARY OF THE TREASURY AND THOSE OF AN ENVOY EXTRAORDINARY TO A FOREIGN POWER ARE SO INCOMPATABLE THAT THEY OUGHT NOT TO BE UNITED IN THE SAME PERSON.

TO ADOPT THE RESOLUTION PROVIDING THAT THE COMMITTEE COMMUN- ICATE TO THE PRESIDENT THE ADVICE OF SENATE THAT THE SECRE- TARY OF THE TREASURY, MR. ALBERT GALLATIN, IS NOT ACCEPTABLE AS A FOREIGN ENVOY.  (P.87)

TO AGREE TO A REPORT REGARDING THE PETITION OF JOSHUA BARNEY AND OTHERS TO OBTAIN RELINQUISHMENT OF THE CLAIM OF THE U. S. TO CERTAIN ENEMY PROPERTY, WHICH REPORT RECOMMENDS, BECAUSE THE MATTER IS BEFORE THE PROPER JUDICIAL TRIBUNALS, THAT FURTHER ACTIONBE POSTPONED UNTIL THE FIRST MONDAY IN DECEMBER NEXT.
TO CONSENT TO THE APPOINTMENT OF WILLIAM DUANE, TO BE ADJU- TANT GENERAL.

TO ORDER ENGROSSMENT AND THIRD READING OF S. 17 (3 STAT. 4, 7/13/1813), A BILL RELINQUISHING THE CLAIM OF THE UNITED STATES  TO CERTAIN GOODS, WARES AND MERCHANDISE, CAPTURED BY PRIVATE ARMED VESSELS.  (P.40A)
TO POSTPONE CONSIDERATION OF S. 17 (3 STAT. 4, 7/13/1813), A BILL RELINQUISHING THE CLAIMS OF THE UNITED STATES TO CER- TAIN GOODS, WARES, AND MERCHANDISE CAPTURED BY PRIVATE ARMED VESSELS.  (P.40B)
